subject: College Athletics
Basketball
lead_paragraph: Chris Douglas-Roberts scored 24 points, Robert Dozier added 19 and the second-ranked Tigers beat No. 5 Georgetown, 85-71, extending the nation’s second-longest home winning streak to 37 games.
